# Solana Exporter Setup – Documentation Steps

---
### ✅ 1. **Install Go (if not already installed)**


`sudo apt update sudo apt install golang-go -y`

Check the version:

`go version`

---
### ✅ 2. **Clone the Exporter Repository**

As user `sol`:

`cd ~ git clone https://github.com/asymmetric-research/solana-exporter.git`

---
### ✅ 3. **Build the Exporter Binary**


`cd ~/solana-exporter/cmd/solana-exporter go build -o ~/solana-exporter/solana-exporter`

Verify it built correctly:


`~/solana-exporter/solana-exporter --help`

---
### ✅ 4. **Run the Exporter (for testing)**


`~/solana-exporter/solana-exporter \   -rpc-url http://127.0.0.1:8899 \   -listen-address 0.0.0.0:9100`

You should see:

nginx


`Starting Solana exporter on 0.0.0.0:9100`

Then test from another terminal:

`curl http://localhost:9100/metrics`

---

### ✅ 5. **(Optional) Configure Firewall to Allow Prometheus Access**

Edit `/etc/nftables.conf` and add this line inside the `input` chain:


`tcp dport 9100 ip saddr 77.200.151.32 accept`

Then reload the firewall:

`sudo nft -f /etc/nftables.conf`

---

### ✅ 6. **(Optional but Recommended) Set Up as a systemd Service**

Create the service unit file:

`sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/solana-exporter.service`

Paste:

`[Unit] Description=Solana Exporter for Prometheus After=network.target  [Service] User=sol WorkingDirectory=/home/sol/solana-exporter ExecStart=/home/sol/solana-exporter/solana-exporter -rpc-url http://127.0.0.1:8899 -listen-address 0.0.0.0:9100 Restart=always RestartSec=3  [Install] WantedBy=multi-user.target`

Enable and start:

`sudo systemctl daemon-reload sudo systemctl enable solana-exporter sudo systemctl start solana-exporter sudo systemctl status solana-exporter`

To check logs:

`journalctl -u solana-exporter -f`




Add for node exporter